OL,3,C#10 million government funding
OL,4,Cconfirmed for Scottish Borders
OL,6,FThe money has been allocated from the
OL,7,F#350 million Borderlands Inclusive
OL,8,FGrowth Deal, which supports projects
OL,9,Facross five local authority areas on
OL,10,Fboth sides of the border.
OL,12,FCouncil leader Cllr Euan Jardine said:
OL,13,F"The Destination Tweed programme aims
OL,14,Fto capitalise on, protect and enhance
OL,15,Fthis incredible asset that we have
OL,16,Frunning through the region and help
OL,17,Fcreate a unique attraction which will
OL,18,Fshare the nature, history and stories
OL,19,Fof the river and surrounding area with
OL,20,Fvisitors from across the world.
